DA  - 1992/09/01
TI  - International Configuration and Coordination Archetypes for Medium-Sized Firms in Global Industries
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 533
EP  - 549
VL  - 23
IS  - 3
AB  - The purpose of this study is to determine the basic configuration and coordination patterns for medium-sized firms competing in global industries. Analyzing 126 businesses competing in nine different global industries, five distinct archetypes are identified. The results suggest that selective globalization—in which the firm defines its global strategy around a narrow subset of the value chain—may lead to the most effective outcomes.
